{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread\/setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/thread\/setthreadsafetychecksenabled(_:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread"]]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets whether the thread safety checks the engine normally performs in methods of certain classes (e.g., "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node"},{"type":"text","text":") should happen "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"on the current thread","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"roleHeading":"Type Method","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot6ThreadC03setC19SafetyChecksEnabledyySbFZ","title":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"enabled","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The default, for every thread, is that they are enabled (as if called with ","type":"text"},{"code":"enabled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" being "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Those checks are conservative. That means that they will only succeed in considering a call thread-safe (and therefore allow it to happen) if the engine can guarantee such safety.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because of that, there may be cases where the user may want to disable them ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enabled"},{"text":" being ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") to make certain operations allowed again. By doing so, it becomes the user’s responsibility to ensure thread safety (e.g., by using "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Mutex"},{"type":"text","text":") for those objects that are otherwise protected by the engine."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is an advanced usage of the engine. You are advised to use it only if you know what you are doing and there is no safer way.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is useful for scripts running on either arbitrary "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" objects or tasks submitted to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkerThreadPool","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". It doesn’t apply to code running during "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node"},{"text":" group processing, where the checks will be always performed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even in the case of having disabled the checks in a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkerThreadPool"},{"text":" task, there’s no need to re-enable them at the end. The engine will do so.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note","name":"Note"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Thread/setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/thread\/setthreadsafetychecksenabled(_:)","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets whether the thread safety checks the engine normally performs in methods of certain classes (e.g., "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":") should happen ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"on the current thread"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread\/setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)","title":"setThreadSafetyChecksEnabled(_:)"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/WorkerThreadPool":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"WorkerThreadPool"}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"WorkerThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/workerthreadpool","abstract":[{"text":"A singleton that allocates some ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"s on startup, used to offload tasks to these threads.","type":"text"}],"title":"WorkerThreadPool","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkerThreadPool","role":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Thread":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Thread","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","title":"Thread","type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A unit of execution in a process."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Thread"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/thread"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Node":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Node"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Node","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node","role":"symbol","title":"Node","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/node","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Base class for all scene objects."}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Mutex":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Mutex","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/mutex","title":"Mutex","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Mutex","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A binary "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Semaphore","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for synchronization of multiple "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"s.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Mutex"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Semaphore":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Semaphore","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Semaphore"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/semaphore","abstract":[{"text":"A synchronization mechanism used to control access to a shared resource by ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Thread","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"s.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Semaphore","title":"Semaphore"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","title":"SwiftGodot","role":"collection","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"}}}